# Project images ‚Äî manual renames (do not auto-rename)

When the owner says they **updated / renamed images**, **reordered WIPs**, or **renamed files manually** in `projects/<folder>/`:

## Do

1. **Read filenames on disk** (`before`, `after`, `hero`, `WIP-###.jpeg` / `.png` only).
2. **Update HTML only** so story pages match those names:

```bash
node scripts/sync-project-story-images.mjs <id> [id ‚Ä¶]
```

That syncs **`index.html`**: Work in progress gallery + project-hero + Open Graph ‚Äî **no file moves**.

3. Optionally run **`publish-webpage.mjs`** for optimize / validate / meta ‚Äî it does **not** rename files, but prefer **`sync-project-story-images.mjs`** when the only change is manual renames (faster, no image processing).

4. `node scripts/sync-projects-gallery-index.mjs <id>` ‚Äî gallery tile thumbnail in `data/projects-index.json`.

5. If the project has numeric **`importance`** in `config.json` (home highlight lead or tile), also run **`node scripts/sync-home-highlights.mjs`** ‚Äî baked `index.html` highlight images/descriptions do not update automatically. Shortcut after image-only changes: run steps 2‚Äì4 for the id(s), then `node scripts/sync-home-highlights.mjs` once to refresh all highlight slots.

## Do not

- **Do not** run **`normalize-project-media-names.mjs`** unless the owner **explicitly** asks to auto-rename loose photos by capture time.
- **Do not** promote a WIP to **`hero.jpeg`** or renumber WIPs to fill gaps ‚Äî that script‚Äôs job, not ‚Äúupdate images after my rename‚Äù.
- **Do not** assume ‚Äúupdate images‚Äù means normalize + full publish.

## Wrong vs right

| Owner intent | Wrong | Right |
|--------------|-------|-------|
| ‚ÄúI renamed the files‚Äù | `normalize-project-media-names.mjs` then `publish-webpage.mjs` | `sync-project-story-images.mjs` |
| ‚ÄúUpdate images on the page‚Äù (after manual folder edit) | Renumber WIPs / create `hero.jpeg` from a WIP | Sync HTML from disk |
| USB ingest / messy loose `IMG_*` files | ‚Äî | `normalize-project-media-names.mjs` **only when asked** |

## Page hero

Story hero / OG use files on disk: **`hero` ‚Üí `after` ‚Üí first `WIP-###` ‚Üí `before`**. If the owner wants a specific shot on top without renaming, they can name it **`hero.jpeg`** themselves ‚Äî the agent must not rename files for them.
